Timing & Speed

--> Paranoid (Slowest)
nmap -T0 <target>
Use when: Trying to avoid intrusion detection systems.

--> Sneaky
nmap -T1 <target>
Use when: Trying to avoid detection, slightly faster than T0.

--> Polite
nmap -T2 <target>
Use when: You want to reduce bandwidth usage on the network.

--> Normal (Default)
nmap -T3 <target>
Use when: Everyday scanning. This is the default if you don't specify.

--> Aggressive (Fast)
nmap -T4 <target>
Use when: Fast scans on a reliable network. Most commonly used speed.

Insane (Fastest)
nmap -T5 <target>
Use when: Speed matters more than accuracy. May miss results.
